description: Red-tailed Hawk. It is a bird species commonly found in North America. The Red-tailed Hawk is known for its distinctive reddish-brown tail. It is a raptor, which means it is a bird of prey. It has broad, rounded wings and a short, wide tail. Red-tailed Hawks mainly feed on small mammals, birds, reptiles, and insects. They are known for their keen vision and powerful talons. Their average lifespan in the wild is around 10 to 21 years. Their wingspan ranges from 45 to 65 inches.
